wotmudmapper.help.room_data = [[ <cyan>Room Data:<reset> These commands are used to view and edit data stored in/around rooms <yellow>listroomdata<reset> - Display data stored for the current room. This will include room description, doors, zone, and any further data you might wish to define and store. <yellow>setroomdata key value<reset> - Set user data in the current room for a key (with no spaces) and an arbitrarily long value. Example: setroomdata herb_load sunburst, setroomdata nohide yes, setroomdata nochannel true, etc. <yellow>getroomdata key<reset> - Display data stored in the current room for the given key <yellow>deleteroomdata key<reset> - Delete the data in the current room with the given key <yellow>deleteallroomdata<reset> - Delete all data stored in the current room. This WILL delete the room description and doors which could cause the map script to not function as well as you might wish <yellow>crz zonename<reset> - Change the zone of the current room to the given name <yellow>cmz zonename<reset> - Change the zone that will be assigned to newly created rooms <yellow>shiftroom direction<reset> - Shift the current room one unit in the given direction <yellow>map zonecolor color<reset> - Change the display color for room zones <yellow>makelabel color position text<reset> - Create a text label with the given color and text at the given position relative to your current room. Possible positions include: n, e, s, ne, se, sw, nw. <yellow>viewcolors<reset> - View a list of possible colors that can be specified in the makelabel command. Opens the relevant mudlet wiki page with the colors. <yellow>setmarker symbol<reset> - Create a marker in your current room with the given symbol.
